[[Captain/Legends|Captain]] '''Ortugg''' was the leader of the nine [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorrean]] guards at [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]].<ref name="GG5">''[[Galaxy Guide 5: Return of the Jedi]]''</ref> He was a member of the [[Groogrun]] clan.<ref name="EGWT" />

==Biography==
[[File:OrtuggRoguaChoked-ROTJ.png|thumb|left|250px|Rogua (left) and Ortugg (right) block Luke Skywalker's path]]
He was known as the "axe-wielder" and worked well with [[Rogua]], a fellow [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorrean]]. Ortugg was uncompromisingly loyal to [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]], as long as he was given food to eat. He was instructed to spy on Jabba's accountant [[Tessek/Legends|Tessek]], due to Jabba's growing suspicions about him.<ref name="GG5" /> During one night he interrupted [[Dannik Jerriko]] when he tried to feed on the soup of [[Yarna d'al' Gargan/Legends|Yarna d'al' Gargan]].<ref name="Gamorrean Guard's Tale">{{StoryCite|story=And Then There Were Some: The Gamorrean Guard's Tale|book=Tales from Jabba's Palace}}</ref>

He and Rogua were present when [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] and [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] entered the palace at the start of the rescue of [[Han Solo]],<ref name="BTM">''[[Star Wars: Behind the Magic]]''</ref> and the pair were later [[Telekinesis/Legends#Choking powers|Force choked]] by [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] when they attempted to block his entrance.<ref name="CCG Choke">{{CCG|set=Jabba's Palace Limited|cardname=Choke}}</ref> He was one of the guards who laughed at [[Jubnuk/Legends|Jubnuk]] as he was eaten by the [[Rancor/Legends|rancor]] when he fell into the pit with Skywalker.<ref name="Jabba's Chef">{{StoryCite|story=Taster's Choice: The Tale of Jabba's Chef|book=Tales from Jabba's Palace}}</ref> Shortly after, he was killed when Jabba's sail barge, the [[Khetanna/Legends|''Khetanna'']], was destroyed by Skywalker and his friends.<ref name="TCSWE" />

[[Venorra]] was member of the same Gamorrean clan as Ortugg.<ref name="Letter">{{WEGCite|story=Ortugg's Letter Home|book=The Star Wars Sourcebook|reprint=1}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Ortugg_SWI_60.jpg|213px|thumb|Ortugg]]
The ''[[Rebellion Era Sourcebook]]'' said Ortugg remained behind at the palace when Jabba died at the [[Sarlacc/Legends|sarlacc]] pit, still waiting for their master and driving off all intruders.<ref name="RESB">''[[Rebellion Era Sourcebook]]''</ref> This contradicts the evidence of other sources, though some Gamorreans may have continued to guard the palace afterwards.<ref name="Gamorrean Guard's Tale" />

